Comment: A Pipe can be used to connect two geographically distinct nodes within a Gas Transmission Network
A PipingNetwork is an agglomeration of Pipes, PipeFittings, and Transmission components that interact over a directed graph
A GasTransmissionNetwork is a sub-class of PipingNetwork and specifically specifies a PipingNetwork for the purposes of transporting large volumes of gas over long distances.
A PipeSegment is the elementary part of Piping. A Pipe is assembled of a number of PipeSegments.
A DirectedConnection is derived from the meta-class DirectedArc and represents the connecting element between Devices
An OutputProduct is Material that is output by a ProcessStep
A CompressionStation is the agglomeration of multiple compressors in a single geographical location
